<br>
&quot;See Calliope, I told you not to worry. My father is a smart man and knows how to handle a situation. Where do you think I got it from?&quot;<br>
<br>
Apollo made is way across the room to Paris and placed his golden arm around the young boy.<br>
He leaned over and shook the hair from his eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Quite a responsibility you've got here. Surely you wouldn't want to anger any of these sultry femmé fatals. And I do warn you, oh handsome Paris, son of Pria-&quot; Apollo stopped himself before he revealed the true lineage of the child.<br>
<br>
&quot;Son of Aegaus, these goddesses are well...no goddesses. They WILL, try to bribe you. With promises of fame, riches, knowledge, beauty, and glory, but I suggest you head my warning and decided with your heart.&quot; and with this Apollo poked the young man's chest.<br>
<br>
 He released the boy and walked away, knowing full well none of his words had really gotten through to him. Apollo could tell by the bedazzled look in his eye that this was far out of his league. Perhaps Zeus wasn't as dim witted as he previously conceived. Nevertheless, this would bring about problems.<br>
<br>
He walked to the side of his father and crossed his arms, a smirk playing upon his face.<br>
&quot;Capital idea old man. Capital idea.&quot;<br>
And with that Apollo stood besides his father, the all-mighty Zeus, Lord of the Heavens, to watch a mere mortal judge perhaps history's first beauty pageant. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 169<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/19/01 8:16:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=143>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Divine Intervention</span><hr size=1> If Hera's eyes could be any colder, she would have frozen the &quot;Sun King&quot; with her look.  With all his flowerly words, she did not care for Apollo's choice in the contest.  As they all spoke her eyes would flit to Aphrodite..true...most desired the Goddess of Love's beauty.  But, Hera's elegance and own ego would not even allow Aphrodite the pleasure of winning.  <br>
Then she listened to Zeus's decision to have a mortal decide on who is the fairest.  Her cold blue eyes turned to Paris.  <br>
The Queen moved with an almost chilling grace towards the handsome young man.  Slowely, she walked around him in her regalness and spoke, &quot;Surely, this young man is wise enough to caste a good judgement over this contest.&quot;  She continued to circle him and then whispered in one of his ears, &quot;To chose the fairest who could give him dominion over the world.&quot;  Her words were quiet so that none could hear. (NONE ok ).<br>
Then as if on air..she glided away from the young man to walk over non-chalantly to speak with the newlyweds. <p>~~<<<<<<{{{{@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/19/01 8:38:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=144>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Trump Card</span><hr size=1> Apollo smiled as everything began to play into his hand. He had placed his pawns in all the rights places. His word was golden, and he managed to walk away unscaved. His blue eyes wandered to his step-mother as she leaned over to whisper to Paris. <br>
<br>
'And the bribes start already. Should've known mother would've used her trump card. She's no fool. Never was, never will be.' Apollo thought to himself.<br>
<br>
His cold stare met his mother's as she glided across the room to the newlyweds. He met her with a stare as cold as her's. He had patented that stare a long time ago, and he wasn't about to let ANYONE, and he ment ANYONE, think themselves above him. He cut his eye at her and walked away, surely she knew how down right foolish and childish she was making herself look.  Like a spoiled brat. Who did she think she was, HIM? Sheesh, he was the only one upon Olympus that could pull off the &quot;Arrogant Little Prince&quot; routine and still make it look good.<br>
<br>
This party was just starting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uaubard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AU Bard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazons Unite Bard</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/20/01 3:07:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=145>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trump Card</span><hr size=1> Paris gulped as the King of the Gods placed the burden of judgement of the fairest upon his shoulders.  He certainly did not want to upset three of the most powerful women in the known world.  His eyes glanced to each of the Goddesses and then back to Zeus, in an almost beckoning look to get out of the task.  <br>
As Hera seemed to stalk around him, he could almost feel the coldness drifting off of her as she stared to Apollo.  And then an almost fake warmth as she turned her frigid blue eyes to his.  Her gift sounded very good actually.  Who would not want to rule the world? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uaubard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AU Bard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazons Unite Bard</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/20/01 3:10:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=146>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> OOC:  More Players</span><hr size=1> Before the war gets going on anymore..if you or anyone would like to play any of the Hero's of the Trojan War.. Please email HeraQofGs@aol.com .   Get her approval first..so that we can keep just one player playing a hero..instead of two.    <br>
