<br>
He walked passed her, blinking his eyes at the perfect moment as if to dismiss Hera with his eyes alone. A smile though, appeared on his face as he approached Paris, the guest of the hour. Apollo shook the hair from his eyes and shook his hand at a servant to fetch him a chair. <br>
Apollo sat in the chair next to Paris and laughed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Quite a view you've got here.&quot; Apollo's brow perked as his eyes bounced from Hera, to Athena, to Aphrodite.<br>
<br>
&quot;You a smart boy. Don't do anything stupid.&quot;<br>
<br>
